Exelon Corporation (Exelon), headquartered in Chicago, IL, is a registered public utility holding company that, through its subsidiaries, operates in two business segments, Energy Delivery and Generation. In addition to the two business segments, Exelon Business Services Company provides Exelon… MoreExelon Corporation (Exelon), headquartered in Chicago, IL, is a registered public utility holding company that, through its subsidiaries, operates in two business segments, Energy Delivery and Generation. In addition to the two business segments, Exelon Business Services Company provides Exelon and its subsidiaries with financial, human resource, legal, information technology, supply management, and corporate governance services.

Exelon Energy Delivery serves about four million electricity customers in Northern Illinois through ComEd and about 1.5 million electricity and 460,000 natural gas customers in Southeastern Pennsylvania through PECO Energy.  Exelon Generation is comprised of three operating groups, Exelon Nuclear, Exelon Power and Exelon PowerTeam.

Exelon acquired Pepco in 2016.
• Excelon's subsidiary, Constellation, acquired the Integrys Energy Services business unit in late 2014.
• Maintains a $100,000 - $250,000 hardware support maintenance contract with CSU.
• Maintains an up to $100,000 telecom expense management contract with Eclipse Telecom.
• Maintains a $1… More• Excelon's subsidiary, Constellation, acquired the Integrys Energy Services business unit in late 2014.
• Maintains a $100,000 - $250,000 hardware support maintenance contract with CSU.
• Maintains an up to $100,000 telecom expense management contract with Eclipse Telecom.
• Maintains a $1 million - $5 million data center operations contract with HP.
• Maintains a $100,000 - $250,000 enterprise applications support (erp, crm, etc.) contract with Onyx.
• Maintains a $250,000 - $1 million infrastructure management contract with Pomeroy and HP.
• Maintains a $250,000 - $1 million infrastructure management contract with TCS.
• Maintains a $5 million - $10 million mobile application development contract.
• Maintains a $250,000 - $1 million legacy application support contract.
• Maintains an up to $100,000 application development contract.
• Maintains a $1 million - $5 million application development contract.
• Maintains a $1 million - $5 million application testing contract.
• Maintains a $100,000 - $250,000 disaster recovery contract.
• Maintains a $100,000 - $250,000 hardware support maintenance contract.
• Exelon Corporation maintains a $1M-$5M data center operations contract with IBM.
• Exelon Corporation maintains a $1M-$5M enterprise applications support contract with Accenture for Customer System.
• Exelon Corporation maintains a $5-$10M telecom expense management contract with Tangoe.

2013 and Earlier:
IT Priorities:
• The company is developing a BYOD policy as well as looking at big data initiatives. 
• Upgrading the company's laboratory information management system(LIMS) using .NET

IT Structure:
• Handles the majority of its Information Technology initiatives through the company's partner, Exelon Business Services Company. 
• A Vice President of IT handles IT specifically for Peco Energy, but takes direction from the parent company's CIO.
• Maintains a group of procurement professionals, known internally as category managers, who are in charge of procurement for IT hardware and IT supply. These individuals oversee contracts with various vendors, including Meridian Technology for IBM, CISCO, and other products.
• The company plans to relocate to Baltimore, MD in 2014 after the merger with Constellations.

IT Intelligence:
2013: 
• Has a five-year contract, valued at over $150 million, with CSC through 2013. According to the agreement, CSC provides Exelon with a broad spectrum of infrastructure support services, including technical support; database administration; telecommunications; storage support; and server management services.





